In which way do people damange our planet?
In my opinion, humans damange the planet in several ways. One major issue is pollution, as factories often discharge toxic waste into rivers and lakes, which harms both ecosystems and human health.
In addition, the extraction of fossil fuels leads to large-scale destruction of natural habitats, as forests are cleared and land is exploited for resources. This, in turn, threatens biodiversity and puts many specicies at risk of extinction.
I also think overconsumption is a key problem, as people tend to use more resources than necessary, which puts further pressure on the environment.

Do you think that the environmental situation will improve in the nearest future?
Yes, I’d like to think so. Environmental issues are becoming more widely recognized, and people are gradually becoming more aware of their impact on the planet.
I believe this growing awareness, along with advances in technology and stronger government policies, could help improve the situation in the near future. However, real progress will depend on whether both individuals and governments take consistent action.

What kinds of pollution are serious in your country?
In my opinion, the most serious types of pollution in Vietnam are air and water pollution. As the country is developing rapidly, industrialization and urbanization have increased significantly.

For example, air pollution is a major issue in big cities due to traffic congestion and emissions from factories. At the same time, water pollution is also a concern, as some industrial waste is discharged into rivers and lakes, affecting both the environment and public health.
